  "text": "In this section, we apply a single upper-solution or lower-solution method and a monotone iterative approach to study problem (1.1), and we obtain some new results on the existence results of unique nonnegative solutions. Let E = C[0, 1] be the Banach space with the norm x = max t∈ [0, [CITATION_1] |x(t)|, and θ denotes the zero element in E. Given the usual normal cone P = {x ∈ E : x(t) ≥ 0, ∀t ∈ [0, 1]}. Then x ≤ y if and only if x(t) ≤ y(t), ∀t ∈ [0, 1]. For x, y ∈ P with x ≤ y, we have x ≤ y . Define",
